“After a transformation that took just over a year, the final results far exceed what the family imagined. “When we look around our home, we feel so fulfilled. Every room has a unique quality, and we love them all,” says @jeanprokos. “We’re reminded every day of the thought and creativity that went into making our home a place to share [and make] beautiful memories with our family and friends.” Davies-Gaetano agrees: “It was such a wonderful reveal with them because it was even more incredible than what they anticipated. For me, that’s the biggest joy.”

What a delight to get lost and mesmerized by the oasis of Umberto Pasti and @stephanjanson. When you tour their homes and gardens, you feel an immense passion for life and the people of Tangier. We had the pleasure of visiting Umberto and Stephan in the city and Rohuna, a small village by the sea. What they are doing for Rohuna and its people is remarkable. Soon. Umberto will be traveling to the US to tour his new book, which is stunning and help support the foundation, so keep an eye out for his schedule. If you can meet him, you are in for a beautiful experience. For more information on how you can support this beautiful cause, please follow @friendsofrohuna. 
Thank you, Umberto and Stephan Jason, for sharing your homes. It has been a true wonder. I will be back! 🧡  @indagarefounder @indagaretravel @archdigest @alevasseur1

I feel very fortunate to have made wonderful new friends during this journey, sharing and seeing together through a collective lens of fascination and curiosity.

“All @odginteriors projects are replete with eye-pleasing materials and carefully considered details.
“I’ve made it my mission to create authentic, soulful design in a bespoke manner,” Ohara says. “We ask our clients lots of questions: ‘What can we do so that every aspect of the design enhances the experience?’ ‘What does it sound like when you are moving through the house?’ ‘Do you like the lights on really bright, as that affects the surface of the walls?’ The materials are integral to what we create and how people connect to the spaces.”

“@odginteriors introduced durable architectural elements outside and in. Some, like the weathered-wood beams for the ceilings, are Old West, but the majority have old-world origins, including the 18th-century rubble stone and reclaimed bricks used for the portico and loggias and the French plaster stucco on the walls. All the flooring is 18th-century reclaimed oak sourced in Europe, and most of the antique bedroom doors are French and Italian.”

Daily, I reflect on my gratitude for the trust of our clients. It is a gift to design bespoke interiors that reflect a personal sense of lifestyle and dreams. I am honored to share this spectacular home, designed for a wonderful family and in collaboration with an incredible team of talent. 
Thank you at @archdigest @amyastley @madeleineluckel @jessnritz for capturing the essence and soul of this beautiful collaboration, telling a story that resonates beautifully with the entire journey. 

Thank you to our incredible clients for their trust and passion for allowing the team to create a home that is defined by the elements that are meaningful to them as a family. Also, a personal thank you to the poetic vision of @kenlinsteadtarchitects. You are a dream to collaborate with. To @alftinconstruction for your meticulous attention to detail and execution, and of course to Janell Hobart of @denlerhobartgardens your gardens are spectacular, creating the most alluring connection to the way you fully experience the property. 

Finally, thank you to my team, for their continued passion and dedication 🤎 I am beyond grateful. XO

“Throughout the interiors, @odginteriors continues this nuanced synthesis of multiple references, thoughtfully creating resonant gestures that “pay respect to their heritage.” A series of wall panels in the primary bedroom depicting a tree-of-life motif was custom screen-printed and embroidered in India by @dascoli_. The ornate imagery “anchors the room” and is also a beautiful tribute to India. Other furnishings and accessories enhance this particular design narrative. “They were really passionate about ideas like that,” Davies-Gaetano says.

With the Holiday upon us and the New Year quickly approaching, it’s time to reflect on this past year. I look forward to the coming days of festive family time and reflection; the gratitude I feel in my heart is immense. This year was full of so many incredible accomplishments for our firm. We installed fantastic projects that were a dream in the making. We started the discovery of new projects with excellent clients and collaborators. Our team has grown and rallied around the opportunities, and I am proud of our team’s growth, passion, and unyielding perseverance. Our client’s trust is something that I hold very precious, and I am grateful for it. It is a true joy to curate bespoke environments for our clients; knowing that the homes we create will be full of holiday joy this festive season is a beautiful thought. 
Happy Holidays to all!
